{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Decoder for the Cambium green-tree snapshot format."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GreenSnapshotDecoder"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Decoded trees carry a freshly-minted "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TokenKeyNamespace"},{"type":"text","text":" that is not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"shared with any builder cache. This is fine for read-only consumption","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(analysis tools, AST printers, wire-format transport) and for one-shot","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"decode-then-discard workflows.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Load-then-edit caveat."}]},{"text":" If the decoded tree will subsequently feed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"GreenTreeBuilder.reuseSubtree(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" from an incremental-parse loop, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"first reuse pays a one-time "},{"code":".remapped","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" slow path: the source resolver’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"namespace doesn’t match any builder’s cache, so dynamic token keys are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"re-interned and the subtree is rebuilt. After that first reparse, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"new tree’s resolver carries the cache’s namespace, and subsequent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reuses fast-path normally.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The total work is the same either way (one O(N) walk in either decode"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or first-reuse). A cache-aware "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"decodeBuildResult"},{"type":"text","text":" that moves the cost"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into the load step is technically straightforward but is "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"deferred"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"until a real parser\/editor consumer measures the first-edit latency"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and decides the rebalance is worth the API surface. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SubtreeReuseOutcome"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from "},{"code":"reuseSubtree","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is the diagnostic signal: a high "},{"code":".remapped","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" rate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"across reparses means the cache lineage is broken (either by this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"decoder or by a missing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"result.intoCache()"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/GreenSnapshotDecoder","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Cambium"}],"title":"GreenSnapshotDecoder","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GreenSnapshotDecoder"}],"externalID":"s:20CambiumSerialization20GreenSnapshotDecoderO","symbolKind":"enum","roleHeading":"Enumeration","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GreenSnapshotDecoder"}],"role":"symbol"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium"]]},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Type-Methods","title":"Type Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/Cambium\/Gre